FBIS3-35212 "drnes035_p_94006" FBIS-NES-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Dostam Militia `Offensive' Defeated in Konduz LD2002184794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002184794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Language: Pashto Article Type:BFN [Text] An offensive by the notorious Dostam militia, which was mounted this morning in western Konduz Province, was defeated. A military correspondent of the Bakhtar Information Agency reports that the infamous Dostam militia, in cooperation with communist generals, early this morning mounted an offensive in Konduz Province's western areas that was completely foiled as a result of the courage shown by the Islamic army and mojahedin of the Konduz Province. Some [words indistinct] of the criminal militia of Dostam. The report adds that all mojahedin of Knoduz Province, in united ranks, are continuing jihad against the notorious militia. Mop-up operations in Konduz Province's districts are continuing by the mojahedin and the faithful local people.
